OL,7,FAs a female farmer, Clodagh said she's
OL,8,Fdetermined to break boundaries too.
OL,10,F"Women have always been in
OL,11,Fagriculture, they've just been in the
OL,12,Fbackground not getting the recognition
OL,13,Fthat they deserve," she said.
OL,15,FShe added: "Up until recent years,
OL,16,Fwomen have come into the spotlight of
OL,17,Ffarming, working first hand with
OL,18,Fcattle, sheep or whatever industry
OL,19,Fthey're in, instead of just being
OL,20,Foverlooked and overshadowed."
